# Renderer UI rules

These files drive the settings / overlay / onboarding UI. They've accumulated
visual drift from rapid prototyping (mixed borders, padding, hardcoded hexes,
repeated inline patterns). These rules stop the drift.

## Tokens, not hardcoded colors

- **Never introduce a new hardcoded hex color** (`#xxxxxx`, `#xxx`, or
  `rgb(...)` literal) in these files. Use tokens from
  `src/renderer/src/styles/tokens.css`.
- If the token you need does not exist, ADD it to `tokens.css` and reference
  it. Name it semantically (`--surface-hover`, not `--gray-200`).
- CI enforces this via `scripts/check-hex-colors.sh` â€” your change will fail
  the build if it introduces new hex literals in this scope.
- Existing hardcoded hexes are tech debt. Prefer replacing them when nearby.
  Never add new ones.

## Component extraction

These files are large and have repeated inline patterns (Card, ToggleRow,
RadioCard, AlertBanner, TabBar, SectionHeader, InfoRow). When you touch one:

- **Do not grow `AIPage.tsx`, `HistoryPage.tsx`, `GeneralPage.tsx`, or
  `App.tsx`** past their current size. If your change adds more than ~20 net
  lines to any of these, extract a component first, then make the change
  against the extracted primitive.
- **If you are about to inline a second copy** of a Card / ToggleRow /
  RadioCard / AlertBanner / TabBar pattern, stop. Extract the first one into
  `src/renderer/src/components/`, add a Storybook story, then use it in both
  places.
- Prefer composition over prop explosion. A component with more than ~6 props
  is a sign that two components want to come out.

## Spec alignment

The active visual direction is
`docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-14-settings-ui-redesign-design.md`. Read
sections 1â€“7 before making visual changes. Warm neutrals + teal-for-purpose.
Section cards, uppercase tracking on section headings, `space-y-6` between
sections.

## Storybook first

When you extract a component, add a story. `pnpm storybook` is the iteration
loop â€” use it. PRs that add components without stories should be rejected.

## Accessibility and tokens

- All interactive elements must have a visible focus state. Tailwind:
  `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent/30 focus-visible:outline-none`.
- Buttons and links need `aria-label` when the label is only an icon.
- Disabled controls need `aria-disabled` in addition to `disabled`.
